#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:234
msgid ""
"``TopicMessageView`` is itself an extension of a ``QObject``. There's lots "
"of things you could do with this using all the might and power of Qt. This "
"is not a python Qt tutorial sadly, `though there are many available online "
"<https://doc.qt.io/qtforpython-6/examples/"
"example_widgets_painting_basicdrawing.html>`_. So we're going to just add a "
"simple QWidget and draw on it. First, add the following imports:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:240
msgid ""
"from python_qt_binding.QtWidgets import QWidget\n"
"from python_qt_binding.QtGui import QBrush, QPainter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:245
msgid "Then update the ``DiagnosticPanel`` class to the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:247
msgid ""
"class DiagnosticPanel(TopicMessageView):\n"
"    name = 'Awesome Diagnostic'\n"
"\n"
"    def __init__(self, timeline, parent, topic):\n"
"        super(DiagnosticPanel, self).__init__(timeline, parent, topic)\n"
"        self.widget = QWidget()\n"
"        parent.layout().addWidget(self.widget)\n"
"        self.msg = None\n"
"        self.widget.paintEvent = self.paintEvent\n"
"\n"
"    def message_viewed(self, bag, entry, ros_message, msg_type_name, "
"topic):\n"
"        super(DiagnosticPanel, self).message_viewed(bag=bag, entry=entry,\n"
"                                                    ros_message=ros_message, "
"msg_type_name=msg_type_name, topic=topic)\n"
"        self.msg = ros_message\n"
"        self.widget.update()\n"
"\n"
"    def paintEvent(self, event):\n"
"        qp = QPainter()\n"
"        qp.begin(self.widget)\n"
"\n"
"        rect = event.rect()\n"
"\n"
"        if self.msg is None:\n"
"            qp.fillRect(0, 0, rect.width(), rect.height(), Qt.white)\n"
"        else:\n"
"            color = get_color(self.msg)\n"
"            qp.setBrush(QBrush(color))\n"
"            qp.drawEllipse(0, 0, rect.width(), rect.height())\n"
"        qp.end()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:279
msgid ""
"In the constructor, we create a ``QWidget`` and override its ``paintEvent`` "
"method. Now when we get a message with ``message_viewed``, we save it, and "
"update the widget, which will in turn call our ``paintEvent``. Do not call "
"``paintEvent`` manually, that has to be done by Qt. Before a message is "
"selected, we'll just paint a white rectangle. Otherwise, we'll draw a "
"circle, using our handy helper method to relate the color to what level the "
"diagnostic is at."
msgstr ""

