#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:338
msgid ""
"Okay, now we actually want to customize how the messages are drawn in the "
"timeline based on the messages themselves. For that, you will need to read "
"and deserialize the messages from the bag file. Here are the new imports:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:342
msgid ""
"from python_qt_binding.QtGui import QPen\n"
"from rclpy.time import Time\n"
"from rclpy.serialization import deserialize_message\n"
"from rqt_bag.bag_helper import to_sec"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:349
msgid "Then update ``draw_timeline_segment()``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:351
msgid ""
"def draw_timeline_segment(self, painter: QPainter, topic, start: float, end: "
"float, x: float, y: int, width: float, height: int):\n"
"    bag_timeline = self.timeline.scene()\n"
"    start_t = Time(seconds=start)\n"
"    end_t = Time(seconds=end)\n"
"\n"
"    for bag, entry in bag_timeline.get_entries_with_bags([topic], start_t, "
"end_t):\n"
"        topic, raw_data, t = bag_timeline.read_message(bag, entry.timestamp, "
"topic)\n"
"        msg = deserialize_message(raw_data, DiagnosticStatus)\n"
"        color = get_color(msg)\n"
"        painter.setBrush(QBrush(color))\n"
"        painter.setPen(QPen(color, 5))\n"
"\n"
"        t_float = to_sec(Time(nanoseconds=t))\n"
"        p_x = int(self.timeline.map_stamp_to_x(t_float))\n"
"        painter.drawLine(p_x, y, p_x, y + height - 1)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:369
msgid ""
"Using the ``topic``, ``start`` and ``end`` parameters of the method, we can "
"get the bag entries that correspond with this segment of the timeline. We "
"can then get the actual message and use it to draw. Here we are drawing a "
"line based on the level of the diagnostic message. We can automatically "
"figure out where to draw the message horizontally using the "
"``map_stamp_to_x()`` method which converts float seconds to widget pixels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:374
msgid "screenshot of rqt_bag with differently colored bars on the timeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Create-An-Rqtbag-Plugin.rst:378
msgid ""
"If computing the message representation on timeline is more computationally "
"demanding, you should use `Timeline Cache <https://github.com/ros-"
"visualization/rqt_bag/blob/rolling/rqt_bag/src/rqt_bag/timeline_cache.py>`__ "
"like the `ImageTimelineViewer <https://github.com/ros-visualization/rqt_bag/"
"blob/rolling/rqt_bag_plugins/src/rqt_bag_plugins/image_timeline_renderer."
"py>`__ does, but figuring that out is left as an exercise to the reader."
msgstr ""
